[The serotype of _E. coli_ in geographic cluster of enterohemorrhagic cases is not stated, nor is whether the isolates have been shown to be genetically related. With an incubation period up to about 12 days or so, unless the reservoir persists in a stored location such as frozen meat, the cluster is likely to remain at this number. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/9Mpn.]
